</figureCitation>
). Antenna serrate from antennomere 
<number box="[547,598,1087,1111]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[614,698,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 60" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[235,1365,234,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 60. Lateral habitus: 53 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 54 C. biolleyi (holotype); 55 C. colburni; 56 C. martiale (paratype); 57 C. milelo (paratype); 58 C. podagricus; 59 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 60 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698655/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[666,698,1086,1111]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons with frontal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1095,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Frontal habitus: 22 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 23 C. biolleyi (paratype); 24 C. colburni; 25 C. martiale; 26 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 27 C. podagricus; 28 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 29 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 30 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698645" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698645/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[1063,1095,1087,1111]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Prothorax. Pronotum with median gibbosity slightly elevated, not divided by longitudinal and transversal sulcus (
<figureCitation box="[236,320,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 60" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[235,1365,234,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 60. Lateral habitus: 53 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 54 C. biolleyi (holotype); 55 C. colburni; 56 C. martiale (paratype); 57 C. milelo (paratype); 58 C. podagricus; 59 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 60 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698655/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[288,320,1158,1183]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral gibbosity slightly elevated; basal lobe with depression and slightly emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1406,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[1375,1406,1158,1183]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Mesothorax and metathorax. Elytra, striae with punctures deeply impressed (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1140,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[1109,1140,1194,1219]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
); less conspicuous teeth at base of striae 
<number box="[313,327,1231,1255]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[386,403,1231,1255]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="4.0">4</number>
; tooth of stria 
<number box="[574,588,1231,1255]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="4.0">4</number>
closer to base of tooth of stria 
<number box="[954,968,1231,1255]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
than to anterior margin of elytra; stria 
<number box="[1422,1436,1230,1255]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="6.0">6</number>
conspicuously impressed. 
<collectingCountry box="[449,505,1266,1291]" name="India" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur (
<figureCitation box="[597,680,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[651,680,1267,1291]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="73.0">73</number>
</figureCitation>
) on external ventral margin with toothed carina; without denticles above of external ventral margin; pecten with 
<number box="[691,705,1303,1327]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="8.0">8</number>
teeth. 
<collectingCountry box="[787,843,1302,1327]" name="India" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia (
<figureCitation box="[921,1006,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[977,1006,1303,1327]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="73.0">73</number>
</figureCitation>
) strongly emarginated beside mucro; lateral coronal denticles present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" box="[199,1436,1374,1399]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Abdomen. Pygidium longer than wide, oval, at median basal region with deeply impressed punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1423,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 43. Pygidium of male: 35 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 36 C. colburni; 37 C. martiale; 38 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 39 C. podagricus; 40 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 41 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 42 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 43 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698649/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,1375,1399]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Male genitalia. Median lobe, ventral valve as long as wide, lateral margin concave on subapical region (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,263,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[202,1385,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 90. Male genitalia, median lobe: 85 Ctenocolum pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 86 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 87 C. acapulcensis; 88 C. janzeni; 89 C. salvini (paralectotype); 90 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698661/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1446,1471]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
), basal margin strongly emarginated. Internal sac, lateral apex with short tuft of setae, hinge sclerite with base curved, short, extending over 
<number box="[492,502,1483,1507]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[513,527,1483,1507]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
of subapical region; subapical region with homogeneously distributed spicules, medially dense in elongated strip; median region with dense spicules forming two irregular elongated groups; submedian region with squamous open ring-shape sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[829,914,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,263,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[202,1384,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[202,1385,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 90. Male genitalia, median lobe: 85 Ctenocolum pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 86 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 87 C. acapulcensis; 88 C. janzeni; 89 C. salvini (paralectotype); 90 C. tuberculatum. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698661/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[883,914,1554,1579]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
); basal region in lateral with sparse denticles. Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[259,346,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 91 – 99" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 91 – 99. Male genitalia, tegmen, lateral lobe: 91 C. aquilus (paratype); 92 C. colburni; 93 C. martiale (holotype); 94 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 95 C. podagricus; 96 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 97 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 98 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 99 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698663/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[315,346,1591,1615]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="97.0">97</number>
</figureCitation>
), lateral lobes separated by emargination about 
<number box="[904,953,1590,1615]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="0.75">0.75</number>
times the length of lateral lobes; internal margin near end of emargination curved, forming a “U”; expanded at apex, about 
<number box="[1098,1112,1627,1651]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="4.0">4</number>
times the smallest width on median region; without membranous projection at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" box="[199,539,1698,1723]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Note. The female is unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1289,1734,1759]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" box="[199,1289,1734,1759]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1734,1759]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<emphasis box="[565,721,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName box="[565,714,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygospilotos">pygospilotos</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
refers to punctures deeply impressed at pygidium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,510,1867]" box="[199,906,1770,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1770,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution.</emphasis>
Neotropical region: 
<collectingCountry box="[585,902,1770,1795]" name="United States Virgin Islands" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">United States Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
